 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.514","title":"[audit][fix] AsyncDbPool::try_get() orphans connection in closed pool on validate_on_checkout","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"ubuntu","created_at":"2026-04-01T19:28:09.557710840Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-01T19:28:13.312228373Z","closed_at":"2026-04-01T19:28:13.311777815Z","close_reason":"FIXED: try_get() popped connection, released lock, then pushed back without checking closed. If close() ran between pop and push, connection was orphaned. Added closed check before push_front.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.514","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-04-01T19:28:09.557710840Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.515","title":"[audit][distributed] RegionBridge snapshots must preserve caller-supplied time","description":"Fresh-eyes child under asupersync-1qfd0. RegionBridge::create_snapshot currently hardcodes Time::ZERO, so sync/replication snapshots lose chronology and sync_state.last_sync_time never reflects a truthful snapshot instant. Thread explicit Time through RegionBridge snapshot/sync paths and federation replication export call sites, preserve bounded scope, add focused regressions for snapshot timestamp propagation and sync_state timestamp tracking, and validate with rch-backed targeted tests/check/clippy plus fmt check.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"Codex","created_at":"2026-04-01T20:31:41.632313835Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-01T21:07:31.776512209Z","closed_at":"2026-04-01T21:07:31.775990339Z","close_reason":"Completed: explicit snapshot time propagation implemented; bridge regressions passed; all-targets check with messaging-fabric passed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","distributed","snapshot"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.515","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-04-01T20:31:41.632313835Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":2918,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.515","author":"Codex","text":"Implemented bounded snapshot-time propagation: RegionBridge sync/create_snapshot/upgrade_to_distributed now take explicit Time, sync/apply_snapshot persist last_sync_time, FederationBridge export_replication_transfer now takes explicit Time, and distributed/fabric/e2e callsites were updated with focused timestamp regressions. Validation so far: rch exec cargo check --lib --features messaging-fabric passed on vmi1293453; exact rch regression test retries are still running; broader all-targets/clippy runs are currently noisy because of unrelated workspace/toolchain and remote-worker issues.","created_at":"2026-04-01T20:52:58Z"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.516","title":"[audit] Fresh-eyes audit of unaudited RNG/random surface","description":"Bounded support slice under the fresh-eyes audit epic. Select one currently unaudited random/RNG-related source file, audit it carefully for correctness and determinism issues, update audit_index.jsonl with the verdict, and only widen to code changes if a concrete bug is found and fixed with targeted rch validation.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":90,"created_at":"2026-04-01T20:41:43.090237616Z","created_by":"DarkCastle","updated_at":"2026-04-01T20:44:27.733135385Z","closed_at":"2026-04-01T20:44:27.732699856Z","close_reason":"Diff audit completed; no bugs found","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","exploration","random"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.516","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-04-01T20:41:43.090237616Z","created_by":"DarkCastle","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":2912,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.516","author":"DarkCastle","text":"Starting bounded fresh-eyes audit slice under asupersync-1qfd0. Initial filename-only scan showed the obvious RNG files (src/util/entropy.rs and src/util/det_rng.rs) are already covered in audit_index.jsonl, so I am broadening to symbol-level discovery to pick a genuinely unaudited random-adjacent source file before touching code or the audit index.","created_at":"2026-04-01T20:42:04Z"},{"id":2914,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.516","author":"DarkCastle","text":"Pivoting this child from filename-based RNG hunting to a diff audit on src/decoding.rs. Rationale: the obvious entropy files are already fully covered, but src/decoding.rs still owns block-seed derivation and has post-audit changes on 2026-04-01 after its last deep audit entry dated 2026-03-29. I am reviewing only the post-audit delta and will either record a clean diff-audit in audit_index.jsonl or fix a concrete regression if one surfaces.","created_at":"2026-04-01T20:43:49Z"},{"id":2915,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.516","author":"DarkCastle","text":"Diff audit result on src/decoding.rs: SOUND. The entire post-2026-03-29 delta is a non-semantic  binding added after renaming  ->  so non-tracing builds still satisfy unused-variable linting while tracing builds retain structured error emission. No change to block-seed derivation, decoder construction, reject mapping, or failure state transitions.","created_at":"2026-04-01T20:44:02Z"},{"id":2916,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.516","author":"DarkCastle","text":"Clarification for the prior note: the reviewed delta in src/decoding.rs is exactly the cfg(not(feature = \"tracing-integration\")) unused-variable binding that keeps non-tracing builds lint-clean after renaming Err(_err) to Err(err). This is semantically inert and does not alter decoding behavior.","created_at":"2026-04-01T20:44:27Z"}]}
-{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.517","title":"[audit] Fresh-eyes batch: raptorq pipeline/proof/regression/rfc6330","description":"Audit src/raptorq/{pipeline.rs,proof.rs,regression.rs,rfc6330.rs} for correctness and edge-case bugs, fix any real defects with focused tests, and update audit_index.jsonl when done. Explicitly avoid src/raptorq/systematic.rs because it is actively reserved by another agent.","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-02T03:38:16.813068163Z","created_by":"BeigeCoast","updated_at":"2026-04-02T04:27:45.665836625Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.517","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-04-02T03:38:16.813068163Z","created_by":"BeigeCoast","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":2921,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.517","author":"BeigeCoast","text":"Retargeted this child from already-audited observability files to the actually unaudited, unreserved RaptorQ slice {pipeline,proof,regression,rfc6330}. Found and patched a concrete issue in src/raptorq/proof.rs: ReceivedSummary::from_received was buffering the full received-symbol multiset just to compute the truncated-preview binding hash, defeating the module's bounded-size proof-artifact design. Replaced that with a streaming deterministic multiset digest and added an order-independence regression test. Validation is running through rch with an isolated CARGO_TARGET_DIR because the default target cache mixes rustc 1.95 and 1.96 artifacts.","created_at":"2026-04-02T03:54:25Z"},{"id":2922,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.517","author":"BeigeCoast","text":"Validation/results update: rch-backed targeted proof tests passed with isolated CARGO_TARGET_DIR=target/codex-rustc196 for the received_summary tests and the replay_verification_rejects_high_esi_divergence_when_received_preview_truncates test. The command rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=target/codex-rustc196 cargo check --all-targets also passed. cargo fmt --check is not globally green because of unrelated formatter drift in src/lab/oracle/evidence.rs, and cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings is currently blocked by a pre-existing unrelated lint in src/service/buffer.rs (clippy significant_drop_tightening). I did not widen this bead into those other surfaces.","created_at":"2026-04-02T04:05:59Z"},{"id":2924,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.517","author":"BeigeCoast","text":"Validation/results update: rch-backed targeted proof tests passed with isolated CARGO_TARGET_DIR=target/codex-rustc196 ( and ).  also passed.  is not globally green because of unrelated formatter drift in src/lab/oracle/evidence.rs, and  is currently blocked by a pre-existing unrelated lint in src/service/buffer.rs (). I did not widen this bead into those other surfaces.","created_at":"2026-04-02T04:27:45Z"}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.517","title":"[audit] Fresh-eyes batch: raptorq pipeline/proof/regression/rfc6330","description":"Audit src/raptorq/{pipeline.rs,proof.rs,regression.rs,rfc6330.rs} for correctness and edge-case bugs, fix any real defects with focused tests, and update audit_index.jsonl when done. Explicitly avoid src/raptorq/systematic.rs because it is actively reserved by another agent.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-02T03:38:16.813068163Z","created_by":"BeigeCoast","updated_at":"2026-04-03T17:37:51.715991482Z","closed_at":"2026-04-03T17:37:51.715497173Z","close_reason":"Completed fresh-eyes audit; fixed RaptorQ receiver auth-fail-open/error-reporting bug in pipeline.rs and recorded audit trail","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.517","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-04-02T03:38:16.813068163Z","created_by":"BeigeCoast","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":2921,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.517","author":"BeigeCoast","text":"Retargeted this child from already-audited observability files to the actually unaudited, unreserved RaptorQ slice {pipeline,proof,regression,rfc6330}. Found and patched a concrete issue in src/raptorq/proof.rs: ReceivedSummary::from_received was buffering the full received-symbol multiset just to compute the truncated-preview binding hash, defeating the module's bounded-size proof-artifact design. Replaced that with a streaming deterministic multiset digest and added an order-independence regression test. Validation is running through rch with an isolated CARGO_TARGET_DIR because the default target cache mixes rustc 1.95 and 1.96 artifacts.","created_at":"2026-04-02T03:54:25Z"},{"id":2922,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.517","author":"BeigeCoast","text":"Validation/results update: rch-backed targeted proof tests passed with isolated CARGO_TARGET_DIR=target/codex-rustc196 for the received_summary tests and the replay_verification_rejects_high_esi_divergence_when_received_preview_truncates test. The command rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=target/codex-rustc196 cargo check --all-targets also passed. cargo fmt --check is not globally green because of unrelated formatter drift in src/lab/oracle/evidence.rs, and cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings is currently blocked by a pre-existing unrelated lint in src/service/buffer.rs (clippy significant_drop_tightening). I did not widen this bead into those other surfaces.","created_at":"2026-04-02T04:05:59Z"},{"id":2924,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.517","author":"BeigeCoast","text":"Validation/results update: rch-backed targeted proof tests passed with isolated CARGO_TARGET_DIR=target/codex-rustc196 ( and ).  also passed.  is not globally green because of unrelated formatter drift in src/lab/oracle/evidence.rs, and  is currently blocked by a pre-existing unrelated lint in src/service/buffer.rs (). I did not widen this bead into those other surfaces.","created_at":"2026-04-02T04:27:45Z"},{"id":2941,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.517","author":"ScarletDog","text":"Fresh-eyes pass found a second concrete issue in src/raptorq/pipeline.rs. RaptorQReceiver::receive_object was prelabeling authenticated=true whenever a SecurityContext existed and silently treating decoder AuthenticationFailed rejections as 'keep waiting', which let strict-mode bad tags degrade into misleading insufficient-symbol behavior. Fixed by verifying same-object symbols at the receiver boundary, failing closed on strict bad tags, and only reporting authenticated=true when consumed symbols were actually verified. Validation: rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=target/codex-rustc196 cargo test -p asupersync test_receive_object_ --lib passed (12/12 receive-object tests). rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=target/codex-rustc196 cargo check --all-targets passed. cargo fmt --check is still globally red on unrelated files, but rustfmt --check src/raptorq/pipeline.rs is clean. cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings hit remote rch worker instability in the cc crate on one worker; retry on a different worker got past that failure and was still running at comment time.","created_at":"2026-04-03T17:37:20Z"}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.517.1","title":"[audit][raptorq] Guard tuple_indices against malformed public LtTuple inputs","description":"Bounded audit slice under asupersync-1qfd0.517. Review src/raptorq/rfc6330.rs for malformed public LtTuple inputs that can violate tuple index invariants or hang in PI-side iteration. Land a fail-closed fix with focused tests and rch-backed validation.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"AmberQuill","created_at":"2026-04-03T17:21:09.444642195Z","created_by":"AmberQuill","updated_at":"2026-04-03T17:36:40.834993500Z","closed_at":"2026-04-03T17:36:40.834601782Z","close_reason":"Completed fail-closed tuple_indices fix and focused rch validation","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.517.1","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.517","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-04-03T17:21:09.444642195Z","created_by":"AmberQuill","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":2938,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.517.1","author":"AmberQuill","text":"Agent Mail registration is currently degraded after a mailbox repair, so I am using beads comments as the durable coordination fallback for this slice. Starting a bounded audit of src/raptorq/rfc6330.rs focused on malformed public LtTuple inputs: tuple_indices() currently trusts d/d1/a/a1 and can silently emit extra indices or loop forever if a malformed tuple has d=0, d1=0, or a1=0 with b1>=P. I am patching this to fail closed with focused regressions and will validate via rch.","created_at":"2026-04-03T17:21:21Z"},{"id":2940,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.517.1","author":"AmberQuill","text":"Landed the fail-closed fix in src/raptorq/rfc6330.rs. tuple_indices() now rejects malformed public LtTuple values with zero degrees, zero steps, or out-of-range starts before it enters the LT/PI walks, which closes the real hang case where a1=0 and b1>=P can spin forever in the PI-side normalization loop. Added focused regressions for zero degrees and zero steps. Validation: rch-backed cargo test -p asupersync --lib tuple_indices_reject_ passed; rch-backed cargo check -p asupersync --lib passed; rch-backed cargo check --all-targets finished clean on the remote worker; cargo clippy --all-targets is currently blocked by unrelated remote worker cache corruption, and the focused lib clippy failure is pre-existing in src/raptorq/pipeline.rs (match_same_arms), not this change. Agent Mail rebuild is still in progress, so I am recording completion here immediately instead of waiting on the mailbox.","created_at":"2026-04-03T17:36:23Z"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.518","title":"[audit][observability] Fresh-eyes audit of src/observability/level.rs","description":"Bounded fresh-eyes audit slice under the existing audit epic. Audit src/observability/level.rs for correctness and edge-case issues, add or tighten tests only if a concrete defect is found, and update audit_index.jsonl with a diff-audit verdict when complete. Keep the scope strictly local to this file unless a real bug forces a minimal adjacent fix.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":60,"created_at":"2026-04-02T04:16:15.675014081Z","created_by":"TanStork","updated_at":"2026-04-02T04:16:54.872102103Z","closed_at":"2026-04-02T04:16:54.871738808Z","close_reason":"Completed: full fresh-eyes audit of src/observability/level.rs; no correctness defects found on current HEAD. Severity ordering, threshold gating, display/parsing, and trait behavior are coherent, so the file is recorded as SOUND in audit_index.jsonl to avoid duplicate re-audits.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","logging","observability"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.518","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-04-02T04:16:15.675014081Z","created_by":"TanStork","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.519","title":"[audit][observability] Fresh-eyes audit of src/observability/context.rs","description":"Bounded fresh-eyes audit slice under the existing audit epic. Trace src/observability/context.rs through its inbound and outbound call flow, check context propagation invariants and edge cases, and only widen to minimal adjacent fixes if a concrete bug is found. Record the final verdict in audit_index.jsonl.","notes":"Flow trace outcome: DiagnosticContext itself looks coherent on current HEAD, but following that observability path into ObservabilityConfig exposed a concrete adjacent bug in src/observability/mod.rs. should_sample() claimed to hash the key before sampling but actually compared the raw low 32 bits, so sequential low-valued keys were deterministically over-sampled. Patched sampling to use a splitmix64-derived unit interval and added a regression test that catches the old accept-every-low-key behavior. rch-backed fmt/test/check/clippy validation is running.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":75,"created_at":"2026-04-02T22:52:51.053532139Z","created_by":"TanStork","updated_at":"2026-04-02T23:03:36.688387400Z","closed_at":"2026-04-02T23:03:36.688003446Z","close_reason":"Completed: traced src/observability/context.rs through Cx and LogEntry integration, found the concrete adjacent bug in src/observability/mod.rs where ObservabilityConfig::should_sample() claimed hash-based sampling but actually thresholded the raw low 32 bits, causing low sequential keys to be deterministically over-sampled. Patched sampling to use a splitmix64-derived unit interval and added config_sampling_hashes_low_sequential_keys. Validation: rch-backed targeted cargo test --lib config_sampling -- --nocapture PASS; rch-backed cargo check --all-targets PASS; rch-backed cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings PASS. Whole-tree cargo fmt --check is still blocked by unrelated pre-existing drift in src/cli/completion.rs; touched files were normalized with rustfmt --edition 2024.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","logging","observability"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.519","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-04-02T22:52:51.053532139Z","created_by":"TanStork","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.52","title":"[audit][websocket] Remove ambient entropy from client frame masking","description":"src/net/websocket/frame.rs currently generates client masking keys with direct getrandom::fill(), and src/audit/ambient.rs treats that as a critical unresolved ambient-authority violation. Replace the frame-mask path with EntropySource plumbing, use Cx entropy where WebSocket client/server/split APIs already have a context, add targeted regressions, and update the ambient-audit catalog/tests so the critical finding is actually retired.","status":"tombstone","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"SilverQuarry","estimated_minutes":60,"created_at":"2026-03-09T18:54:49.707067660Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-23T07:08:35.747405470Z","closed_at":"2026-03-23T07:08:35.747405470Z","close_reason":"Completed: websocket masking entropy now flows through EntropySource/Cx; rch cargo check --all-targets and focused websocket/audit lib tests passed; repo-wide clippy frontier is unrelated in http_client/debounce","source_repo":".","deleted_at":"2026-03-23T07:08:35.747380313Z","deleted_by":"system","delete_reason":"merge deletion","original_type":"bug","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","determinism","security","websocket"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.52","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T18:54:49.707067660Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.52.1","title":"[audit][websocket] Repair encode_with_entropy borrow call sites after entropy plumbing","description":"The in-progress ambient-entropy websocket changes updated FrameCodec::encode_with_entropy to take &Frame, but several call sites in src/net/websocket/frame.rs, src/net/websocket/client.rs, and src/net/websocket/split.rs still pass Frame by value. That leaves the repo uncompilable and blocks rch-backed validation for unrelated work. Apply the minimal borrow-site fixes only, preserve the existing entropy-plumbing changes, add no new behavior beyond restoring compilation, and validate with rch-backed targeted cargo commands.","status":"tombstone","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"CoralCompass","created_at":"2026-03-09T19:10:35.862874674Z","created_by":"AmberHarbor","updated_at":"2026-03-23T07:08:29.966871456Z","closed_at":"2026-03-23T07:08:29.966871456Z","close_reason":"Current tree already satisfies bead contract; websocket encode_with_entropy call sites already borrow frames","source_repo":".","deleted_at":"2026-03-23T07:08:29.966849596Z","deleted_by":"system","delete_reason":"merge deletion","original_type":"bug","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.52.1","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.52","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T19:10:35.862874674Z","created_by":"AmberHarbor","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":2476,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.52.1","author":"CoralCompass","text":"Audit result: current tree already satisfies this bead.\n\nSource evidence:\n- `src/net/websocket/frame.rs:393` still defines `FrameCodec::encode_with_entropy(&self, frame: &Frame, ...)`.\n- `src/net/websocket/frame.rs:774` already borrows in the encoder implementation (`self.encode_with_entropy(&frame, ...)`).\n- Client-side websocket call paths already borrow frames at `src/net/websocket/client.rs:438`, `:463`, `:485`, `:591`, and `:597`; the helper that reaches the codec also takes `frame: &Frame` at `src/net/websocket/client.rs:603`.\n- Split-side websocket call paths already borrow frames at `src/net/websocket/split.rs:292`, `:437`, `:548`, and `:577`; the helpers that reach the codec take `frame: &Frame` at `src/net/websocket/split.rs:444` and `:584`.\n- File-local formatting check passed: `rustfmt --edition 2024 --check src/net/websocket/frame.rs src/net/websocket/client.rs src/net/websocket/split.rs`.\n\nConclusion: the borrow-site repair described by this bead is already present in the current tree; no code change required.","created_at":"2026-03-10T05:45:41Z"}]}
