+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.524","title":"[audit][observability] ObligationTracker must use RuntimeState logical time without timer driver","description":"src/observability/obligation_tracker.rs currently computes obligation ages from TimerDriverHandle::now() and falls back to Time::ZERO when no timer driver is attached. In timerless runtimes and direct RuntimeState tests that advance state.now, this suppresses age/leak reporting by collapsing active obligations to zero age. Align the tracker with TaskInspector's clock-source rule: prefer timer-driver time when present, otherwise fall back to RuntimeState::now. Add focused regression coverage for timerless logical time and timer-driver precedence. Validation must use rch for any cargo-heavy commands.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-03T16:49:12.723780629Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-03T16:54:27.838545501Z","closed_at":"2026-04-03T16:54:27.838048848Z","close_reason":"Fixed timerless obligation-age leak detection fallback in src/observability/obligation_tracker.rs; added timerless-logical-time and timer-driver-precedence regressions. rch cargo check -p asupersync --lib passed. rch cargo test/clippy for the new tests are currently blocked by unrelated compile/lint failures in src/lab/network/harness.rs, which is under another agent's active remote-runtime reservation.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","observability","time"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.524","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-04-03T16:49:12.723780629Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.525","title":"[audit][service] Gate tower-only Cx provider surface behind feature instead of dead_code scaffold","description":"src/service/service.rs currently compiles CxProvider, ThreadLocalCxProvider, and FixedCxProvider even when feature=\"tower\" is disabled, then suppresses the resulting unused-surface warnings with #[allow(dead_code)] comments that describe them as scaffold-only service Cx integration API. These provider types are only re-exported and meaningful under the tower adapter surface. Gate the provider trait/types/tests to feature=\"tower\" so the public contract matches the compiled surface, remove the dead_code scaffold allowances, and validate with rch-backed cargo commands.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-03T17:03:26.349334725Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-03T17:10:04.134538210Z","closed_at":"2026-04-03T17:10:04.134005530Z","close_reason":"Closed: gated tower-only Cx provider surface in src/service/service.rs and removed dead_code scaffold allowances. Validation via rch: cargo check -p asupersync --lib PASS; cargo check -p asupersync --lib --features tower PASS. rch cargo clippy -p asupersync --lib --features tower -- -D warnings is still blocked by unrelated existing lints in src/lab/network/harness.rs (significant_drop_tightening, needless_pass_by_ref_mut). Focused rch cargo test -p asupersync --lib cx_provider_tests --features tower remained silent on the remote worker after compilation and did not return a final result within the session window.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","service","tower"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.525","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-04-03T17:03:26.349334725Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.53","title":"[audit][service] Make LoadBalancer::call_balanced honor Service::poll_ready","description":"LoadBalancer::call_balanced() clones a backend and invokes service.call(req) directly without first driving Service::poll_ready on that clone. That violates the Service contract and can break middleware-backed services that reserve tokens/permits/state in poll_ready (e.g. rate/concurrency limiters or any custom service that arms itself there). Patch src/service/load_balance.rs so balanced dispatch only calls backends that have been polled ready on the exact clone being used, add focused regressions for a backend that panics if call happens before poll_ready, and validate with rch-backed fmt/check/clippy/test commands.","status":"tombstone","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"CobaltRidge","created_at":"2026-03-09T18:55:18.665997964Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-23T07:08:16.761662812Z","closed_at":"2026-03-23T07:08:16.761662812Z","close_reason":"Implemented LoadBalancer::call_balanced poll_ready fix with regressions; crate lib check/clippy pass via rch, lib tests currently blocked by pre-existing src/web/session.rs E0382","source_repo":".","deleted_at":"2026-03-23T07:08:16.761631023Z","deleted_by":"system","delete_reason":"merge deletion","original_type":"bug","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","load-balance","service"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.53","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T18:55:18.665997964Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.54","title":"[audit][server] Give ConnectionManager a deterministic time getter","description":"ConnectionManager in src/server/connection.rs records ConnectionInfo.connected_at with raw Instant::now(), which keeps the known ambient-time finding in src/audit/ambient.rs alive and makes active connection metadata impossible to drive deterministically in tests. Replace ConnectionInfo timestamps with asupersync::types::Time, add ConnectionManager::with_time_getter() alongside the existing constructor, stamp registrations through the configured clock, and add focused regression coverage proving connected_at can be driven without wall-clock time. Ambient catalog update may need coordination because src/audit/ambient.rs is currently reserved by another agent.","status":"tombstone","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"FoggyGorge","estimated_minutes":45,"created_at":"2026-03-09T19:19:57.684650669Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-23T07:08:19.508139611Z","closed_at":"2026-03-23T07:08:19.508139611Z","close_reason":"Completed via current-tree verification: src/server/connection.rs already uses Time-based connected_at plus ConnectionManager::with_time_getter() and deterministic test coverage. Validation now passes on this slice with rustfmt check on src/server/connection.rs, rch cargo check -p asupersync --lib (exit 0), and rch cargo test -p asupersync --lib connection_manager_time_getter_controls_connected_at -- --nocapture (1 passed). Broad rch clippy -p asupersync --lib -- -D warnings remains blocked only by unrelated repo-frontier lints in src/net/tcp/stream.rs, src/runtime/scheduler/local_queue.rs, and src/transport/router.rs.","source_repo":".","deleted_at":"2026-03-23T07:08:19.508093526Z","deleted_by":"system","delete_reason":"merge deletion","original_type":"bug","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["ambient","audit","determinism","server"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.54","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T19:19:57.684650669Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":2462,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.54","author":"FoggyGorge","text":"Implemented deterministic connection registration timing in src/server/connection.rs by replacing ConnectionInfo.connected_at Instant with asupersync::types::Time, adding ConnectionManager::with_time_getter() while preserving new() as the wall-clock default, and adding deterministic registration coverage in connection_manager_time_getter_controls_connected_at. Validation: local rustfmt --edition 2024 --check src/server/connection.rs => pass. rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch-target-foggygorge-conn-check cargo check --all-targets => blocked by unrelated existing workspace frontier in src/net/websocket/client.rs, src/net/websocket/split.rs, and src/web/session.rs (E0308/E0599/E0728/E0382). rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch-target-foggygorge-conn-test cargo test --lib connection_manager_time_getter_controls_connected_at -- --nocapture => blocked by unrelated existing lib-test compile error in src/web/session.rs:984 (borrow of moved MemoryStore). Ambient catalog cleanup in src/audit/ambient.rs is still pending coordination because that file is reserved by another agent.","created_at":"2026-03-09T19:20:27Z"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.55","title":"[audit][dns] Give DnsCache a deterministic time getter","description":"DnsCache currently uses ambient Instant::now() for insert/expiry/eviction logic, which bypasses the project time-capability patterns and forces sleep-based tests. Add an injectable time getter and deterministic regressions.","status":"tombstone","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"BoldEagle","created_at":"2026-03-09T19:33:15.124291456Z","created_by":"BeigeHorizon","updated_at":"2026-03-23T07:08:28.796561284Z","closed_at":"2026-03-23T07:08:28.796561284Z","close_reason":"Verified complete on main: DnsCache already has with_time_getter plus deterministic no-sleep regressions; rch-backed dns cache test suite passed (13/13).","source_repo":".","deleted_at":"2026-03-23T07:08:28.796538222Z","deleted_by":"system","delete_reason":"merge deletion","original_type":"bug","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","determinism","dns"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.55","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T19:33:15.124291456Z","created_by":"BeigeHorizon","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
