 {"id":"asupersync-v2ofj7.3","title":"[STUB][Track C] Macro surface contract totalization","description":"## Background\nAsupersync already supports proc-macro-based `scope!`, `spawn!`, `join!`, and `race!`, but the audited surface still contains permanently broken macro exports (`try_join!`, `quorum!`) and needs a clean statement of what the supported macro contract actually is in proc-macro and no-proc-macro builds.\n\n## Scope\n- Freeze the supported macro set.\n- Resolve exported placeholder macros.\n- Align remaining fallback/docs/re-exports with the chosen contract.\n\n## Why this matters\nA public macro that exists only to fail at expansion time is documentation debt baked into the API surface.","acceptance_criteria":"1. The supported macro surface is explicit across proc-macro-enabled and proc-macro-disabled builds.\n2. `try_join!` and `quorum!` no longer exist as permanent placeholders.\n3. `join!` / `race!` fallback behavior, re-exports, and docs match reality.","notes":"This track reuses the existing `try_join!` and `quorum!` beads rather than replacing them, but their framing is updated from \"probably delete\" to \"resolve according to the macro contract decision bead\".\n\nValidation charter:\n- Every child implementation bead in this track must finish with comprehensive unit coverage for happy-path, edge-case, boundary, and failure-path behavior.\n- Every child implementation bead that changes runtime-observable behavior must also land at least one deterministic E2E or integration script that exercises the real workflow and the most important failure modes.\n- Validation artifacts for this track must emit structured logs with, at minimum: `scenario_id`, touched feature/profile flags, seed or fixture id, config snapshot, exact command, expected outcome, observed outcome, and artifact/replay pointers.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-03T01:21:30.960906039Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-03T03:15:55.890065304Z","closed_at":"2026-04-03T03:15:55.889685478Z","close_reason":"All children complete: C1 (macro contract defined), C2/C3 (try_join!/quorum! removed), C4 (join!/race! fallback docs aligned).","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-v2ofj7.3","depends_on_id":"asupersync-v2ofj7","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-04-03T01:21:30.960906039Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-v2ofj7.3.1","title":"[STUB][C1] Define supported macro contract across proc-macro and no-proc-macro builds","description":"## Background\nAsupersync needs one clear statement of which combinator macros are genuinely supported, which require proc macros, and what no-proc-macro builds are supposed to expose. This bead makes that contract explicit.\n\n## Technical approach\n- Audit the intended macro surface (`scope!`, `spawn!`, `join!`, `race!`, `try_join!`, `quorum!`, others if present).\n- Decide which macros are first-class supported APIs.\n- Decide whether unsupported macros are removed, implemented, or hidden behind honest cfg behavior.\n- Define documentation and fallback behavior rules for no-proc-macro builds.\n\n## Test / validation plan\n- Verify the chosen contract matches current proc-macro exports and root re-exports.\n- Ensure downstream C2-C4 beads each have a single target outcome.","acceptance_criteria":"1. Supported macro set is frozen.\n2. Proc-macro and no-proc-macro behavior is explicit for each relevant macro.\n3. C2-C4 have unambiguous implementation targets.","notes":"This is intentionally a contract bead, not just an implementation bead. The real bug is user-facing ambiguity.\n\nDownstream validation contract:\n- This decision bead must leave its downstream implementation beads with explicit requirements for comprehensive unit tests, deterministic E2E or integration scripts, and structured validation logs.\n- Any scope or contract decision made here must be reflected in those downstream validation obligations so later implementers do not have to infer the test story.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"SapphireHill","created_at":"2026-04-03T01:25:00.831602687Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-03T03:11:14.687483818Z","closed_at":"2026-04-03T03:11:14.687125583Z","close_reason":"Re-closing: was completed by prior agent. Macro contract defined.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-v2ofj7.3.1","depends_on_id":"asupersync-v2ofj7.1.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-04-03T01:29:38.916207414Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"asupersync-v2ofj7.3.1","depends_on_id":"asupersync-v2ofj7.3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-04-03T01:25:00.831602687Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-v2ofj7.3.2","title":"[STUB][C4] Align join!/race! fallback docs and reexports with the final macro contract","description":"## Background\nEven after `try_join!` and `quorum!` are resolved, the remaining macro surface can still be misleading if `join!`/`race!` docs, fallbacks, and re-exports do not match the contract frozen in C1.\n\n## Technical approach\n- Align `join!` and `race!` fallback behavior with the chosen proc-macro/no-proc-macro contract.\n- Fix any stale docs, re-exports, examples, or compile-error guidance.\n- Ensure the combinator macro surface reads as one coherent API.\n\n## Test / validation plan\n- Build checks in both default and no-proc-macro configurations as applicable.\n- Search/docs/examples review for stale macro guidance.","acceptance_criteria":"1. `join!` / `race!` fallback behavior matches the final macro contract.\n2. Docs/re-exports/examples are aligned with reality.\n3. The macro surface no longer mixes honest APIs with stale guidance.\n4. Comprehensive unit tests cover the changed happy paths, edge cases, boundary conditions, and failure paths introduced by this bead.\n5. Deterministic E2E or integration script coverage exists for the user-visible or cross-component workflow changed by this bead, with structured logs capturing `scenario_id`, feature/profile flags, seed or fixture id, config snapshot, exact command, expected outcome, observed outcome, and artifact or replay pointers.","notes":"This bead is intentionally downstream of the placeholder macro decisions. It is the polish pass that turns a set of fixes into one consistent API contract.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-03T01:29:27.462265391Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-03T03:00:18.287624973Z","closed_at":"2026-04-03T03:00:18.287135093Z","close_reason":"Aligned join!/race! fallback docs and compile_error guidance with the frozen macro contract; remaining no-default-features failures are unrelated pre-existing dead_code debt","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-v2ofj7.3.2","depends_on_id":"asupersync-3eztk2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-04-03T01:29:42.148302084Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"asupersync-v2ofj7.3.2","depends_on_id":"asupersync-6yj6zn","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-04-03T01:29:43.627687589Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"asupersync-v2ofj7.3.2","depends_on_id":"asupersync-v2ofj7.3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-04-03T01:29:27.462265391Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"asupersync-v2ofj7.3.2","depends_on_id":"asupersync-v2ofj7.3.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-04-03T01:29:41.330371601Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
