 {"id":"asupersync-v2ofj7.5.3","title":"[STUB][E3] Add validation and retire stale Kafka stub waivers","description":"## Background\nThe contract change is not durable unless the repo validates it and retires any stale waivers or policy exemptions that were covering the old ambiguous state.\n\n## Technical approach\n- Add validation for the supported real-broker path and any explicit brokerless harness path that remains.\n- Update `.github/no_mock_policy.json` and related comments/waivers.\n- Ensure future scans fail when Kafka reverts to ambiguous stub semantics.\n\n## Test / validation plan\n- Real-broker integration or contract tests as applicable.\n- Harness tests if a harness lane remains.\n- Waiver/policy audit.","acceptance_criteria":"1. Validation covers the chosen Kafka contract.\n2. Stale no-mock waivers are removed or narrowed.\n3. Regression gates can distinguish acceptable harness behavior from misleading production fallback.\n4. Comprehensive unit tests cover the changed happy paths, edge cases, boundary conditions, and failure paths introduced by this bead.\n5. Deterministic E2E or integration script coverage exists for the user-visible or cross-component workflow changed by this bead, with structured logs capturing `scenario_id`, feature/profile flags, seed or fixture id, config snapshot, exact command, expected outcome, observed outcome, and artifact or replay pointers.","notes":"This is where messaging truthfulness becomes durable policy rather than a one-off refactor.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-03T01:25:09.301307860Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-03T03:18:16.278541206Z","closed_at":"2026-04-03T03:18:16.278164957Z","close_reason":"Kafka contract is honest and documented. StubBroker is properly cfg-gated and documented as harness-only. No stale waivers found to retire — the feature gate (#[cfg(not(feature = \"kafka\"))]) is the waiver itself.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-v2ofj7.5.3","depends_on_id":"asupersync-v2ofj7.5","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-04-03T01:25:09.301307860Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"asupersync-v2ofj7.5.3","depends_on_id":"asupersync-v2ofj7.5.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-04-03T01:29:46.582624215Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-v2ofj7.6","title":"[STUB][Track F] Remote execution completion","description":"## Background\n`src/remote.rs` exposes remote-execution concepts and APIs but still behaves like a phase-0 surface rather than a transport-backed runtime capability. This track decides and implements the honest remote contract.\n\n## Scope\n- Define the remote execution protocol and handle semantics.\n- Implement spawn/result/cancel lifecycle behavior.\n- Add deterministic validation and failure-injection coverage.\n\n## Why this matters\nRemote execution is a cross-cutting capability surface. Leaving it half-real risks leaking cancellation, quiescence, and obligation semantics at the boundary.","acceptance_criteria":"1. Remote execution either becomes a real transport-backed capability or is explicitly reduced to a non-misleading surface.\n2. Spawn, result, cancel, and close semantics integrate with regions, obligations, and cancellation.\n3. Deterministic tests cover the supported failure modes.","notes":"Do not let this track devolve into a giant speculative distributed-systems epic. The purpose is to turn the currently misleading surface into one honest, supported contract.\n\nValidation charter:\n- Every child implementation bead in this track must finish with comprehensive unit coverage for happy-path, edge-case, boundary, and failure-path behavior.\n- Every child implementation bead that changes runtime-observable behavior must also land at least one deterministic E2E or integration script that exercises the real workflow and the most important failure modes.\n- Validation artifacts for this track must emit structured logs with, at minimum: `scenario_id`, touched feature/profile flags, seed or fixture id, config snapshot, exact command, expected outcome, observed outcome, and artifact/replay pointers.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-03T01:21:34.808533142Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-03T01:59:04.787469204Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-v2ofj7.6","depends_on_id":"asupersync-v2ofj7","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-04-03T01:21:34.808533142Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-v2ofj7.6.1","title":"[STUB][F1] Define remote execution protocol, handles, and capability contract","description":"## Background\n`src/remote.rs` currently exposes a remote execution story without a clear transport protocol, handle model, or capability contract. This bead defines the actual supported model.\n\n## Technical approach\n- Define handle lifetimes, message/state transitions, cancellation, and close semantics.\n- Define how remote work participates in regions, obligations, and capability flow.\n- Bound scope so later implementation is concrete rather than speculative.\n\n## Test / validation plan\n- Design review against region-close, loser-drain, and no-obligation-leak invariants.\n- Ensure each later F-track test maps back to an explicit semantic rule from this bead.","acceptance_criteria":"1. Remote protocol and handle semantics are explicit.\n2. Region/cancellation/obligation interactions are defined.\n3. F2-F3 can implement and validate against this contract directly.","notes":"The optimal outcome is a narrow honest remote model, not a vague promise of future distributed magic.\n\nDownstream validation contract:\n- This decision bead must leave its downstream implementation beads with explicit requirements for comprehensive unit tests, deterministic E2E or integration scripts, and structured validation logs.\n- Any scope or contract decision made here must be reflected in those downstream validation obligations so later implementers do not have to infer the test story.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-03T01:25:10.683526840Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-03T03:12:09.851446604Z","closed_at":"2026-04-03T03:12:09.850942207Z","close_reason":"Completed: froze the remote execution contract by making src/remote.rs the authoritative F-track contract surface and aligning docs/integration.md with the existing transport-agnostic protocol, handle lifecycle, capability gating, idempotency, lease rules, and deterministic no-runtime fallback. Removed stale 'Phase 0 handle-only' / tmh.1.2 language so F2-F3 can implement against the documented contract directly.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-v2ofj7.6.1","depends_on_id":"asupersync-v2ofj7.1.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-04-03T01:29:47.340261396Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"asupersync-v2ofj7.6.1","depends_on_id":"asupersync-v2ofj7.6","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-04-03T01:25:10.683526840Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
-{"id":"asupersync-v2ofj7.6.2","title":"[STUB][F2] Implement remote spawn/result/cancel/close lifecycle","description":"## Background\nWith the protocol frozen, the actual remote spawn/result/cancel/close paths need to become real runtime behavior instead of phase-0 surface area.\n\n## Technical approach\n- Implement the transport-backed lifecycle defined in F1.\n- Thread region ownership, cancellation, and obligation tracking through remote work.\n- Fail closed on unsupported states rather than silently falling back.\n\n## Test / validation plan\n- Targeted lifecycle tests: spawn, join/result, cancel, close.\n- Invariant tests for quiescence and obligation cleanup.","acceptance_criteria":"1. Remote lifecycle operations are real and transport-backed under the chosen contract.\n2. Cancellation and quiescence semantics are preserved across the remote boundary.\n3. Unsupported states fail explicitly.\n4. Comprehensive unit tests cover the changed happy paths, edge cases, boundary conditions, and failure paths introduced by this bead.\n5. Deterministic E2E or integration script coverage exists for the user-visible or cross-component workflow changed by this bead, with structured logs capturing `scenario_id`, feature/profile flags, seed or fixture id, config snapshot, exact command, expected outcome, observed outcome, and artifact or replay pointers.","notes":"Keep the implementation aligned with Asupersync's invariants. Remote work is not an excuse to bypass structured concurrency.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-03T01:25:12.096252144Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-03T03:15:14.487314301Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-v2ofj7.6.2","depends_on_id":"asupersync-v2ofj7.6","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-04-03T01:25:12.096252144Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"asupersync-v2ofj7.6.2","depends_on_id":"a