 {"id":"asupersync-v2ofj7.6.3","title":"[STUB][F3] Build deterministic remote harness and failure-injection validation","description":"## Background\nRemote execution is especially likely to regress in edge cases. This bead builds the deterministic harness and failure-injection coverage needed to keep the new contract reliable.\n\n## Technical approach\n- Add deterministic harness coverage for remote lifecycle flows.\n- Add failure-injection cases for disconnects, cancellation races, and protocol violations.\n- Ensure replayable evidence exists for failures.\n\n## Test / validation plan\n- Deterministic harness tests.\n- Failure-injection scenarios with reproducible seeds/artifacts.","acceptance_criteria":"1. Remote execution has deterministic coverage for supported lifecycle flows.\n2. Failure modes are tested and reproducible.\n3. Track Z can rely on this bead for remote validation evidence.\n4. Comprehensive unit tests cover the changed happy paths, edge cases, boundary conditions, and failure paths introduced by this bead.\n5. Deterministic E2E or integration script coverage exists for the user-visible or cross-component workflow changed by this bead, with structured logs capturing `scenario_id`, feature/profile flags, seed or fixture id, config snapshot, exact command, expected outcome, observed outcome, and artifact or replay pointers.","notes":"This bead is the guardrail against rebuilding a half-real remote system that only works on the happy path.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-03T01:25:43.642794197Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-03T01:59:23.711473956Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-v2ofj7.6.3","depends_on_id":"asupersync-v2ofj7.6","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-04-03T01:25:43.642794197Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"asupersync-v2ofj7.6.3","depends_on_id":"asupersync-v2ofj7.6.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-04-03T01:29:48.886103617Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-v2ofj7.7","title":"[STUB][Track G] Session-type runtime realization","description":"## Background\nThe session-type layer currently advances typestate but does not actually send or receive over any transport. That makes the API look stronger than the runtime behavior.\n\n## Scope\n- Choose the transport/capability bridge for session channels.\n- Implement real send/recv semantics.\n- Validate typed protocol behavior end-to-end.\n\n## Why this matters\nSession types are only meaningful if the runtime behavior matches the protocol progress they claim to represent.","acceptance_criteria":"1. Session-type channels no longer act as typestate-only echo stubs.\n2. Transport behavior, capability requirements, and close/error semantics are explicit.\n3. Integration tests prove protocol progress over the real chosen bridge.","notes":"Keep the track focused on making the existing API honest. If a narrower initial transport bridge is the right step, document that explicitly rather than pretending the surface is generic before it really is.\n\nValidation charter:\n- Every child implementation bead in this track must finish with comprehensive unit coverage for happy-path, edge-case, boundary, and failure-path behavior.\n- Every child implementation bead that changes runtime-observable behavior must also land at least one deterministic E2E or integration script that exercises the real workflow and the most important failure modes.\n- Validation artifacts for this track must emit structured logs with, at minimum: `scenario_id`, touched feature/profile flags, seed or fixture id, config snapshot, exact command, expected outcome, observed outcome, and artifact/replay pointers.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-03T01:21:36.189172857Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-03T04:27:14.312423860Z","closed_at":"2026-04-03T04:27:14.312038925Z","close_reason":"done","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-v2ofj7.7","depends_on_id":"asupersync-v2ofj7","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-04-03T01:21:36.189172857Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-v2ofj7.7.1","title":"[STUB][G1] Choose the session-type transport and capability bridge","description":"## Background\nThe session-type API cannot become real until it has a concrete runtime bridge. This bead chooses how session channels bind to transport/capability machinery.\n\n## Technical approach\n- Decide the transport abstraction and capability requirements for session channels.\n- Define send/recv/close/error semantics at the runtime boundary.\n- Bound the first supported bridge clearly rather than pretending universal transport support.\n\n## Test / validation plan\n- Check the chosen bridge against typestate promises and runtime invariants.","acceptance_criteria":"1. Session-type runtime bridge is explicit.\n2. Capability and lifecycle requirements are frozen.\n3. G2-G3 have a concrete target contract.","notes":"The clever move here is explicit scope control. A narrower real bridge beats a generic fake one.\n\nDownstream validation contract:\n- This decision bead must leave its downstream implementation beads with explicit requirements for comprehensive unit tests, deterministic E2E or integration scripts, and structured validation logs.\n- Any scope or contract decision made here must be reflected in those downstream validation obligations so later implementers do not have to infer the test story.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"ubuntu","created_at":"2026-04-03T01:25:45.118524810Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-03T03:45:38.901533649Z","closed_at":"2026-04-03T03:45:38.901166226Z","close_reason":"done","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-v2ofj7.7.1","depends_on_id":"asupersync-v2ofj7.1.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-04-03T01:29:49.647633211Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"asupersync-v2ofj7.7.1","depends_on_id":"asupersync-v2ofj7.7","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-04-03T01:25:45.118524810Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}

